The 26-year-old had been due to fight Alexander Ustinov in July, but following the news about his uncle he chose to withdraw. 

Hughie's brother, Peter, said in a statement: 'Sadly we lost out big brother today after 11 weeks of struggle.

'Life will never be the same again for all out family, especially his wife and children. The loss we feel makes us numb with grief. 

'He's passed over to the blessed Lord and one day we will meet again our brother, love you always.' 

He also tweeted: 'Thanks to every one for the nice messages for my brother. God bless all of you.' 

